a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes f g :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
assumes h0 : "\<forall> x. f x = 2 * x + 1"
and h1 : "\<forall> x. g x = f (2 * x) - 3"
shows  "g (g 2) = 22"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Let $f(x) = 2x+1$ and $g(x) = f(2x) - 3$. What is $g(g(2))$? The final Answer is 22
 ### Proof
 Note that $g(x) = f(2x) - 3 = (2 \cdot (2x) + 1) - 3 = 4x - 2$.
 Thus, $$g(g(2)) = g(4 \cdot 2 - 2) = g(6) = 4 \cdot 6 - 2 = \boxed{22}.$$
 *)

theorem
fixes f g :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
assumes h0 : "\<forall> x. f x = 2 * x + 1"
and h1 : "\<forall> x. g x = f (2 * x) - 3"

 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
